There may or may not more food there than you expected, but it is somewhere to get some small vegetables (no fruits), red beans, oil, salt, bread, eggs, toilet paper, sunglasses, fresh juice, coconut balls with sesame seeds, kitchen cleaning products, and packets of stay fresh helpless aid and mutilated kids. Most importantly, it is a chance to say “Bonjour” and walk away with your dignity intact. You don’t have to buy anything, you can see the sense of community and the giving voluntarily charity. And you will get Anisy to answer you in an Afro-Comoros European Creole.

Thats all for now. Peace Be With You 😉

Iain

SIDE NOTE:

Today is Christian Mothering Sunday, where are you brilliant mothers out there receiving chocolates and flowers at church, that you got the kids to hand out? Kidding… Tomorrow is the equivalent Muslim celebration. When you give someone a gift on Islamic Mothering Day, the same as you would on Christian Mothering Day, you have to hand it them yourself, because you can’t expect the gunpoint. After one year of marriage, the Muslims cook us a meal with that month’s most digest, and still manage to trick my inlaw
